Harvey: He's not dying, he lost his job. He has to look for another one. Which, if he hadn't chosen to fight for his company in the first place, would have happened anyway. Now, show me that you get it, go back through those bylaws again, and see if you missed anything. Okay?

Louis: So this is what happens when you promote the wrong guy to senior partner.
Harvey: If you hadn't gone to Stensland behind my back, this wouldn't have happened.
