Harvey: The client is McKernon Motors, not Stensland.
Jessica: You didn't let me finish. Without my consent. That trumps the "who's the client" part. (to Louis) Louis, go to Stensland, repair the relationship. Say what you have to, call it a misunderstanding. Promise Harvey is no longer involved.
Louis: Consider it done.
Harvey: Wait a second. Louis didn't go to Stensland behind my back. You send him there to hedge your bets. Either Stensland's out and we double our billings, or you have plausible deniability, and he stays with the firm.
Jessica: Wow. Am I smart enough to do that?
Harvey: If I win, I look great. If Louis wins, he looks great. Either way... You look great.
Jessica: You mean the firm looks great. Harvey, what I've been trying to get into your head is that you bought in. You are the firm.
Harvey: (smiles) That's it.

Harvey: Mike, follow me. I need you to go talk to Dominic.
Mike: What? Why? Stensland's already CEO.
Harvey: That won't matter if we just buy the damn company.
Mike: What?

Mike: Why are you still working?
Dominic: It's one of my creations. I'm not leaving it unfinished. What the hell do you want?
Mike: I'd be happy to tell you if you put that wrench down.
Dominic: Yeah, you quit with the jokes. I'm the guy who just got fired.
Mike: (sighs) You're right, I'm sorry. What would you say if I told you we could get your job back and stick it to Stensland?
Dominic: I'm done with Harvey and his plans, yeah?
Mike: You were there. We got fired too.
Dominic: You and Harvey still have jobs? He doesn't care about anybody but himself—including you, Mike.
Mike: Yeah. You're probably right. But he did stick his neck out to keep your company here, and he does have an idea that requires your help. So, you can stay here and call him an asshole, or you can come with me and we can help him.
Dominic: Give me my goddamn shirt.

Harvey: You know, it goes from 0 to 60 in the blink of an eye.
Laurence: Did you bring me down here to tell me I can drive this?
Harvey: Better. For $250 million, you can own it.
Laurence: McKernon Motors is for sale?
Harvey: If we act fast.
Laurence: I'll need to see the financials.
Harvey: You put together a letter of intent, they'll get you the financials.
Laurence: You know, their real asset is engine quality. I don't want to just buy the name.
Harvey: Speak of the devil. Laurence, I'd like you to meet the man responsible for every McKernon Motors engine ever built.
Laurence: Wow, Dominic Barone. Very nice to meet you.
Dominic: Good to meet you. I'd like to show you something if you have a minute.
Laurence: Absolutely.

Mike: So? How do we get an offer to the board before they vote to ratify the deal tomorrow?
Harvey: You're gonna go through those bylaws, and you're gonna figure something out.
Mike: I don't have to look through them to figure it out, because I just did.
Harvey: Well, what took you so long? You trying to look like me?
(Mike fixes his hair)

Louis: Each of you have 24 hours to review the documents in front of you, so at this time— (Harvey, Mike and Dominic enter the room)
Robert: Uh, excuse me. Excuse me. What is he doing here?
Louis: I'm sorry. I'm gonna take care of this.
Robert: No, no, I will. (to Harvey) You gentlemen have no right to attend this meeting.
Harvey: Actually, we do. The bylaw states that any original employee has the right to petition the board any time they meet. Dominic Barone has assigned that right to me.
Laurence: He was fired. He no longer has that right.
Mike: Per section 17-5, Point "C," Dominic wasn't given three days' notice, so technically he wasn't fired.
Harvey: Which is why I do have the right to urge the board to accept the offer for the purchase of McKernon Motors. Now, I can tell you that this offer will keep manufacturing here and save jobs while retaining the flagship engine that put this company on the map but I don't have to, because it happens to be for way more goddamn money than the one in front of you right now. Hey Bob, how are ya?

Harvey: It's funny how you held out on me on that proper notice exception.
Mike: I didn't hold out. I made that up on the spot.
Harvey: Really, on the spot? Remember that getting it stuff?
Mike: I know, right? I'm getting it.
Harvey: Well, I was gonna say that, but now you ruined it. That's one thing you definitely get. How to ruin it.
Mike: (mocks) How to ruin it.
Harvey: I heard that.

Devon: I have to admit, you don't suck.
